NIPAH ENCEPHALITIS, HUMAN - BANGLADESH: (RANGPUR) (03)
******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Tue 15 Feb 2011
Source: The Daily Star [edited]
<http://www.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=174246>


Nipah encephalitis claimed 2 more lives at Rangpur Medical College
Hospital (RMCH) yesterday [14 Feb 2011] raising the death toll to 33.
One 8-year-old boy died at about 2:30 am while another, age 4, of
Banshbari village in Lalmonirhat Sadar upazila, [died] around 10:00
am, said RMCH Director Arifur Rahman. They were admitted to the
hospital with high fever on Saturday [12 Feb 2011].

Since 31 Jan [2011], Nipah claimed the lives in 7 districts --
Rangpur, Kurigram, Lalmonirhat, Nilphamari, Gaibandha, Dinajpur and
Kushtia.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail


[The Nipah virus infections and deaths continue to slowly mount in
this area of Bangladesh. The report does not indicated if the exposure
to Nipah virus was from consumption of contaminated date juice or from
eating fruit that the virus hosts, the giant fruit bat _Pteropus_, had
been eating and had contaminated.

An image of a _Pteropus_ fruit bat can be found at
<http://rpmedia.ask.com/ts?u=/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3d/Pteropus_giganteus_fg01.JPG/180px-Pteropus_giganteus_fg01.JPG>.
Location of Rangpur is shown at:
<http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_oId83uoocVI/SK--UYHeoQI/AAAAAAAAADo/uamlcXE_P8g/s400/rangpur+bangladesh.jpg>
A map of the districts of Bangladesh is available at
<http://www.miraebd.net/demo/Bangladesh%20Maps.htm>.
The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Bangladesh can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/r/0r8x>. - Mod.TY/JW]
